                                             "displayName":  "Risky Users Detected - Weekly Summary",
                                             "description":  "This rule give us a weekly summary of users detected to be at risk, so you have to go through the list and do the needed investigation (Investigating the userâ€™s sign-in logs) to further take an action whether to dismiss the user risk or confirming that the user was compromised.\nYou can check whether the user was added to the whitelist after a recent alert, or if there was an email that been sent before and the customer confirmed the expectation of the triggered alert. This will help you in your investigation and in taking the decision of dismissing the user risk.\n \nWe can view the users at risk by navigating to Microsoft EntraID â€”\u003e click on Security under Manage â€”\u003e choose Risky users under Report\n \nDo not forget to filter on all Risk level as â€œLowâ€ not applied by default",
                                             "severity":  "Low",
                                             "enabled":  false,
                                             "query":  "AADRiskyUsers \r\n| where TimeGenerated \u003e ago(7d) \r\n| where RiskState contains \"atRisk\" \r\n| summarize any(RiskLevel) by UserDisplayName",
                                             "queryFrequency":  "P7D",
                                             "queryPeriod":  "P7D",
                                             "triggerOperator":  "GreaterThan",
